Immunosensor using GCE/N-CQDs/Ab1/BSA/AFP/NH2-G@Ab2 was employed to detect different concentrations of AFP under the optimal conditions (Fig. 5
                        ). And the equation of the calibration curve is I = 6876–2703.67log[c], R = 0.979. With the increase of AFP concentration within the range from 0.01 to 100 ng/mL, the ECL intensity decreased linearly. The limit of detection (LOD) was estimated to be 3.3 pg/mL. The lower LOD might be attributed to the factor that the large specific area of N-CQDs could be used to immobilize large amounts of Ab1. Table 1
                         illustrated that the immunosensor described here had a lower detection limit and a more broad linear range than the previously described immunosensors.
